{{Infobox river | name = Boyanska reka | image = Boyanawaterfall.JPG | image_size = | image_caption = Boyana waterfall | source1_location = | mouth_location = [[Perlovska]] | mouth_coordinates = {{coord|42.6816|23.3157|display=it|region:BG_type:river}} | progression = {{RPerlovska}} | subdivision_type1 = Country | subdivision_name1 = [[Bulgaria]] | length = | source1_elevation = | mouth_elevation = | discharge1_avg = | basin_size = | tributaries_left = | tributaries_right = }} The '''Boyanska reka''' ({{lang-bg|Боянска река}}, "[[Boyana]] river") is a river in western [[Bulgaria]], a left tributary to the river [[Perlovska]].
The river flows from the northern slopes of [[Cherni Vrah]] on [[Vitosha|Vitosha Mountain]], crossing [[Torfeno Branishte]] Nature Reserve; at the northern foothills of Vitosha the river drops forming the Boyana waterfall and then crosses the village of [[Boyana]] (part of [[Sofia]], from which the river takes its name) to flow into [[Perlovska]] near the [[National Palace of Culture]] in Sofia.
